If you are going through a tough time, I want you to know that it is not permanent. You are not alone. So many are on the same boat, same journey. Believe that you can get through it, believe in yourself. Do it for yourself. And you will. I love you. Sending you hugs. 🤗

PS- I know therapy is a luxury,I’ve been lucky to have access. I hope somehow those who need it will get it too & if you do, submit to the process,be honest to your therapist cause they can only help you when you’re honest.
I wish this world would be kinder so I start with me.🤗

I have been in therapy for the last 6 months. It has changed me & my life as a result, in ways I could have never imagined. I feel happiness. True happiness. I feel connections. I feel like me,the one I taught to hide cause I wanted to protect her. This is me & she is beautiful💕

Growing up I never was taught self compassion or self love, I was such a depressed kid. I would always have random anger outbursts which I still do, however rare now. Because there’s so much within that I never was allowed to express. I’m teaching that kid she is safe now.

It’s not selfish to love you, to be kind to you. And most of all Forgiving yourself. You must forgive yourself for the past. We are all flawed. We are bound to fail. We are human. But despite what the world taught you & how the world responded to your truth, you must BE YOURSELF.

Love yourself before you expect someone else to love you. They should only be an addition to your world, they can’t make you feel complete, you have to feel complete in yourself. Self love is hard, self compassion harder, coming from a society that terms it as Selfishness.

The time you waste worrying or the energy you invest in other, thinking about others, stressing about others, give some of that time to yourself, learn to meditate. It’s hard, trust me I’ve been there, I used to rant about how meditate is stupidity and I couldn’t be more wrong.

But trust me, those movie tickets are not gonna do you better than therapy, or that junk food you ordered online. Skip a few of these, not saying you have to completely stop these things, but use the same money for Therapy.

It takes a lot of hardwork to reach here but trust me it will all be worth it and so much more. The best investment you’ll ever make is the investment you make in yourself. I know Therapy is expensive, Yoga & Meditation seem dumb & ineffective & you feel its too hard.
Healing is so beautiful, the most beautiful feeling ever. You’ll feel light as a feather, you can actually feel things like the breeze, the sunlight, nature 💕
